31
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:43,359
Yes, one, two. Thanks.

32
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:48,360
When I called yesterday evening,
no one answered.

33
00:04:49,359 --> 00:04:51,759
No, damn...

34
00:04:57,080 --> 00:04:59,679
Shit!

35
00:05:00,279 --> 00:05:02,640
Is anybody home?

36
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:05,559
Don't shout.
John Jr's asleep with a fever.

37
00:05:10,479 --> 00:05:11,760
-Hi.
-Hi.

38
00:05:11,840 --> 00:05:15,879
-Hope it's nothing serious, then.
-No, it's just a cold.

39
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:19,080
Yeah...

40
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:24,080
-How was Gothenburg?
-Zandor got drunk as usual.

41
00:05:24,159 --> 00:05:27,320
But we sold the new novel well anyway.

42
00:05:27,399 --> 00:05:30,200
The booksellers think he's so colorful.

43
00:05:31,239 --> 00:05:34,239
-Have you started smoking?
-No. Why?

44
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:37,920
Why? There's a butt here, a slim More.
The same that Carl smokes.

45
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:41,360
Really? I don't know.

46
00:05:41,439 --> 00:05:44,559
-It must be Tina.
-So, she's started smoking again?

47
00:05:44,640 --> 00:05:47,919
Sorry, I have to go to the store.
I haven't bought dinner.

48
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:52,280
-I called earlier, but no one answered.
-No, I was at the pharmacy.

49
00:05:52,359 --> 00:05:55,560
-You weren't going to work at all.
-Inger got sick.

50
00:05:57,039 --> 00:06:00,240
But I answered when you called
at 02:30 the other night.

51
00:06:00,320 --> 00:06:04,560
Yeah, but I had to call George.
Los Angeles, six hours.

52
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:09,440
It's very strange you don't
have his number in your phone book.

53
00:06:09,519 --> 00:06:14,079
-You wrote it when he was here last fall.
-I forgot it at the office.

54
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:22,080
At Hasse's place, they have a video,
and we saw a horrible film

55
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:26,799
about a guy who shot another guy
in the foot so it exploded.

56
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:30,120
